title: $:/plugins/commons/yjs/CreateWikis
caption: Create Wikis

You can create new wikis here. Select the edition and then enter a name.

Wiki names should be able to contain any unicode characters, although there may
be errors in some browsers which do not support unicode urls.
So ðŸ’© is a valid wiki name.

See
[[creating new wikis|$:/plugins/commons/yjs/Documentation/Creating New Wikis]]
for more information about making wikis.

Create a wiki from

<$radio
  tiddler='$:/temp/NewWiki'
  field='method'
  value='edition'
>
  an edition
</$radio> <<helpButton $:/plugins/commons/yjs/AboutCreateFromEdition>>
<br>
<$radio
  tiddler='$:/temp/NewWiki'
  field='method'
  value='file'
>
  an html file
</$radio> <<helpButton $:/plugins/commons/yjs/AboutCreateFromHTML>>
<br>
<$radio
  tiddler='$:/temp/NewWiki'
  field='method'
  value='tiddlers'
>
  existing tiddlers
</$radio> <<helpButton $:/plugins/commons/yjs/AboutCreateFromTiddlers>>
<br>
<$radio
  tiddler='$:/temp/NewWiki'
  field='method'
  value='node'
>
  a node wiki
</$radio> <<helpButton $:/plugins/commons/yjs/AboutCreateFromNode>>
<br>
<$radio
  tiddler='$:/temp/NewWiki'
  field='method'
  value='duplicate'
>
  duplicate an existing wiki
</$radio> <<helpButton $:/plugins/commons/yjs/AboutDuplicateWiki>>

